</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Piano Sonata No. 5 (Scriabin)</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:172px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Skrjabin_Alexander.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Skrjabin_Alexander.jpg/170px-Skrjabin_Alexander.jpg" width="170" height="191" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Skrjabin_Alexander.jpg/255px-Skrjabin_Alexander.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Skrjabin_Alexander.jpg/340px-Skrjabin_Alexander.jpg 2x" data-file-width="403" data-file-height="453" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Skrjabin_Alexander.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>
Alexander Nikolayevich Scriabin (1872-1915)</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <b><a href="/wiki/Piano_Sonata" title="Piano Sonata" class="mw-redirect">Piano Sonata</a> No.5</b>, Op. 53, is work written by <a href="/wiki/Alexander_Scriabin" title="Alexander Scriabin">Alexander Scriabin</a> in 1907. This was his first sonata to be written in one movement, a format he retained from then on. A typical performance lasts from 11 to 12 minutes.</p>
<p></p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
<div id="toctitle">
